# led_ring

Driver for a **12-LED WS2812B ring** using the Espressif `led_strip` IDF component
(RMT peripheral back-end).

## Hardware connection

| LED ring pin | ESP32-C3 GPIO |
| ------------ | ------------- |
| DI (data in) | GPIO 21       |
| VCC          | 5 V           |
| GND          | GND           |

> **Note:** WS2812B signal level is nominally 5 V, but ESP32-C3 3.3 V output
> is usually accepted.  Add a level shifter if you experience glitches.

## IDF component dependency

`led_strip.h` comes from the `espressif/led_strip` managed component declared in
`src/idf_component.yml`.  No changes to `platformio.ini` are required.

## API

```c
// Initialise the RMT-backed LED strip.
//   led_gpio  — GPIO connected to DI
//   count     — total number of LEDs in the ring (12)
//   offset    — index shift so that position 0 maps to physical "12 o'clock"
void led_ring_init(int led_gpio, int count, int offset);

// Render clock hands:
//   red  pixel at  (hour % 12 + offset) % count
//   green pixel at (minute / 5 + offset) % count
//   overlapping position shows yellow (r + g)
void led_ring_show_clock(uint8_t hour, uint8_t minute, uint8_t brightness);

// Render a linear bar graph — val/max_val fraction of LEDs lit in (r,g,b).
// Used by the settings UI to show current value on the ring.
void led_ring_show_bar(uint8_t val, uint8_t max_val,
                       uint8_t r, uint8_t g, uint8_t b);
```
